						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 12[2]1, Vikāri, Makara (Tai) = 1299 A.D., December.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and fragmentary.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of 30 sheep, which yielded annually 1(1/2) <hi rend="italic">māḍai</hi> to the <hi rend="italic">Baṇḍāram</hi> by a certain Ambalaninaindār Perumāppiḷḷai of Marudūr and they were received by a certain Pōdagaiyaṉ, son of Pammaṉ Bōyiṇḍaṉ. Other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
